Vendor Managed Inventory (VMI) Services




               [click to enlarge]
Vendor Managed Inventory

 

At Lawrence Screw, we make your business our business. With a variety of vendor managed inventory services, we'll help you find the system that works best for you. And because 99 percent of our inventory is customer specific, we carry what you need - and we store it for you, too. Lawrence Screw takes care of the logistics, no matter the product, to bring you tangible results, including:

Increased Productivity
               Reduced Waste
               Reduced Inventory
               Reduced Operational Costs






Because we take care of everything from quality checking to recycling, you can enjoy a streamlined procurement process-and a competitive advantage. With warehouse locations in Illinois, Louisiana, Mississippi, Texas, Oklahoma, Wisconsin, China, and Puerto Rico, we're rapidly expanding our global presence to better serve you, wherever you may be.
Lawrence Screw programs are technology-based systems designed to incorporate manufacturing principles into your inventory replenishment process. Lawrence Screw truly manages inventory based on our customers' usage and adjusts inventory levels based on demand, ensuring you have the parts you need to run your business.
We offer custom service based on customer requirements. Lawrence Screw provides flexible VMI Systems that can be developed to meet each customer's needs.
Vendor Managed Inventory (VMI): Eliminates non-value-added activities like receiving, inspection, and material handling while reducing inventory.
Lawrence Screw's 3rd Party Logistics (3PL): Customer-specific warehousing helps us manage any customer product needs, while utilizing the Lawrence Screw method of supply which provides visibility to the category spend via our customized reporting and other measuring tools. 3PL allows cooperation between the customer's selected vendors and Lawrence Screw. This results in supplier reduction while maintaining technical contact with customer-trusted vendors.
Lawrence Screw manages materials for customers worldwide. We help to save our customers time and money by:

Reducing inventory levels and investment
   Reducing the floor space required for storing inventory
   Giving back resources being used in the procurement process for class "C" items
   Eliminating shortages by gaining control over inventory fluctuations due to seasonal demand or special job consumption fluctuations
   Improving Supply Chain Management and consolidating suppliers
   Streamlining Accounting processes with consolidated invoices & monthly billing
   Reporting and Performance Metrics

 
Lawrence Screw has the best reporting capabilities in the industry. The following list of reports is just a sampling of what we provide to our customers:

Exception Reports
   Inventory Valuation Reports
   Usage Reports
   Non-Usage Reports
   Inventory Turns
   Defective Parts Per Million
   On-Time Delivery
   System Overview


